info.title: Vocera AI API
info.description: Complete API documentation for Vocera AI Platform. This API provides endpoints for managing AI-powered conversations, call analytics, and quality monitoring features.

get.description:
Manage call logs.

This view provides endpoints to retrieve, delete, and list call logs for external users.
A call log represents a record of a communication event, including details such as the agent involved,
the call ID, and the outcome of the call. This information is crucial for monitoring and evaluating
the performance of agents and the quality of interactions.

Required only when call_logs is "all" OR is number of first N calls. Only either of agent_id or assistant_id is required

parameters.name: call_ended_reason__in
parameters.description: Multiple values may be separated by commas.

parameters.name: id__in
parameters.description: Multiple values may be separated by commas.

parameters.name: customer_number__in
parameters.description: Multiple values may be separated by commas.

parameters.name: call_id__in
parameters.description: Multiple values may be separated by commas.

parameters.name: call_ids
parameters.description: Comma-separated list of call log IDs (e.g., 1,2,3)

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: A page number within the paginated result set.

parameters.name: page_size
parameters.description: Number of results to return per page.

the performance of agents and the quality of interactions.
